&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post Title&lt;/strong&gt; Rotational Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Service&lt;/strong&gt; Community Wide&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Borough&lt;/strong&gt; Trafford&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band &amp; salary scale&lt;/strong&gt; 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours of work &lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hrs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent/Fixed term&lt;/strong&gt; permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are Trafford Local Care Organisation - an exciting, new public sector organisation bringing together NHS community health services and adult social care services in Trafford. We’re driven by the aim of improving the health of local people in Trafford by working across organisational boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our community healthcare teams in adults and children&#39;s services are employed by Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust and deployed to us, linking closely with our colleagues in Manchester Local Care Organisation. Our teams work as one and together we will make a massive difference to the health of people in Trafford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for an enthusiastic and adaptable qualified Occupational Therapist to join our varied community based rotation that covers the following settings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neuro Rehabilitation/ Stroke&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Urgent Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intermediate Care in- patient beds&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Equipment and Adaptations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outpatient Rehabilitation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paediatrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rotations are for six months. Support and encouragement to develop is provided via a band 5 support group, regular supervision, in service training and monthly Occupational Therapy meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Requirements of the Person Specification:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience within the NHS is essential. Experience within the community NHS is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is a community post you must hold a UK drivers Licence and have access to a car.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
